        <updateDate>2020-06-11T18:03:50Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Corporate Accountability Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires corporations that receive federal aid related to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) to (1) provide at least 14 days of fully paid leave to all workers, (2) pay each employee a wage of not less than $15 an hour, and (3) limit CEO and executive pay.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
